improvement:
Replace the incomplete connection code block with the complete version:
```javascript
for (let j = i + 1; j < particles.length; j++) {
  if (connections >= maxConnections) break;

  const p2 = particles[j];
  const dx = p.x - p2.x;
  const dy = p.y - p2.y;

  if (Math.abs(dx) > connectionDistance || Math.abs(dy) > connectionDistance) continue;

  const dist = Math.hypot(dx, dy);

  if (dist < connectionDistance) {
    connections++;
    const opacity = (1 - dist / connectionDistance) * 0.3;
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(p.x, p.y);
    ctx.lineTo(p2.x, p2.y);
    ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(249, 115, 22, ${opacity})`;
    ctx.stroke();
  }
}
```

Add cleanup in the useEffect return function:
```javascript
return () => {
  cancelAnimationFrame(animationId);
};
```
Also add `animationId = requestAnimationFrame(draw);` after the draw() call and move `createParticles()` to run inside the draw function or as a separate init function to avoid recreating particles on every resize.

Replace `Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy)` with `Math.hypot(dx, dy)` for better performance.

